HEADWORD: Telestich
<hw>Te*les"tich</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ the end +
<?/ a line, verse.]</ety> <def>A poem in which the final letters of the
lines, taken consequently, make a name. Cf. <er>Acrostic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
